    "The scatterplot depicts each point representing the query or key version of a word, denoted by the point color.",
    "Attention head visualization helps in pruning by allowing the identification of redundant or less informative attention heads that can be pruned without significantly affecting the model's performance [30].",
    "Heads with fewer clusters of search results tend to demonstrate more semantic behavior, whereas heads with dispersed results tend to focus more on token position.",
    "Hence, pruning will mainly affect the heads that are not capturing semantic and contextual representations as well as heads that are not in the higher layers.to the attention heads present in the model.",
    "For example, in the case of BERT-Base, which has 768 hidden units and 12 attention heads, each attention head's size is 64."
